Description: Allocation ID is the unique job id or workload id.
It is unique for each project. Science domain or project domain can be extracted by initial english characters substring from alphanumeric string.
The username of the user submitting the job
Time when the execution of a job begins or jobs actually start.
Time when a job is completed.
Duration of the job execution in seconds
Time when the job is submitted in the job queue.

Number of nodes requested for the job. For job size: Leadership jobs are the ones that have more than 5645 nodes. Large jobs have more than 1882 nodes but less than 5645 nodes. Medium Jobs run on 92 nodes or more but less than 1882 nodes. Small jobs have less than 92 nodes.
Status of the job when completed. Successfule jobs have 'completed' status. Use <> 'completed' for failed or incomplete jobs.
Reason of the status of the jobs
